# Idempotency Patterns

Idempotent operation design for EWM Robotic Platform P0 improvements.

## Auto-Apply Triggers
- When implementing SAP order unique index (P0 #3)
- When building Dify callback idempotency (P0 #21)
- When designing retry mechanisms for failed API calls
- When preventing duplicate task creation from MQTT messages
- When adding X-Idempotency-Key headers to POST endpoints

## Activation Commands
→ "Add unique index to SAP order table to prevent duplicate orders"
→ "Implement Dify callback idempotency with Redis caching"
→ "Make MQTT task dispatch handler idempotent using task_id deduplication"
→ "Add X-Idempotency-Key header requirement for all POST endpoints"

## EWM Idempotency Requirements
- SAP order sync: Unique constraint on order_id
- Dify callbacks: Redis-based idempotency with 1-hour TTL
- MQTT task dispatch: Task ID deduplication
- POST endpoints: Require X-Idempotency-Key header
- Database: Unique indexes at DB level (not just application)
- Race conditions: Use Redis distributed locks
- Monitoring: Track duplicate request hit rates
